THIERY Jean-Paul Course in Embryology July 2-3, 1988
REFERENCE LIST 
EMBRYOLOGY
An introduction to EMBRYOLOGY (1981) Balinsky Saunders
College Publishing may be there is a newer edition.
The Neural Crest Nicole Le Douarin (1982). Cambridge
University Press
ADHESION MOLECULES
The Cell in Contact "Adhesions and Junctions as
Morphogenetic Determinants" Edelman G.M. and Thiery,
.P. Editors (1985). John Wiley and Sons, New York.
A new book should appear in the fall title "Morphoregulatory
Molecules".
Edelman, G.M. (1986). Cell adhesion and the molecular
processes of morphogenesis. Ann. Rev. Cell Biol. 2: 81-1 16.
Edelman, G.M. (1988). Biochemistry, "Morphoregulatory
Molecules"
Edelman, G.M. (1987). CAMS and Igs: Cell adhesion and the
evolutionary origins of immunity. Immunological Reviews,
100: 1 1-45.
Hynes, RO. 1986). Fibronectins. Scientific American, 254:
32-41.
Hynes, R.O. 1987). integrins: A family of cell surface
receptors. Cell 48: 549-554.
Hynes, R.O. 1985). Molecular biology of fibronectin. Ann.
Rev. Cell Biol. 1: 67-90.
Hemler, M.E. (1988). Adhesive protein receptors on
hematopoietic cells. Immunolog today, 9: 109-1 13.
Obara, M., Kang, M.S., Yamada, K.M. (1988). Site directed
mutagenesis of the cell binding domain of human
fibronectin: Separable, synergistic sites mediated Adhesive
Function. Cell: 53: 649-657.
IMMUNOLOGY
Le Douarin, Dieterlen-Lievre, F., and Oliver, P.D.
(1984). Ontogeny of primary organs and 
stem cells. Amer. J. Anat. 170: 261-299.
Le Douarin, N.M., Jotereau, F.V., Houssaint, E., and Thiery,
.P. (1984). Primary organ ontogeny in birds. In
"Chimeras in Developmental Biology". Le Douarin, .M. and
McLaren, A. eds. Academic Press. London, pp. 179-216.
